    Adjusting batch effects 

    obj$set_batch(batch = c("1", "2", "4"))
#> WARN  [2022-09-26 16:55:20] Only using samples from batch(es) 1Only using samples from batch(es) 2Only using samples from batch(es) 4
obj$set_type(type = "X")
#> WARN  [2022-09-26 16:55:20] Only using samples of type X
g_pre <- obj$plot_pca()
#> WARN  [2022-09-26 16:55:20] Removed -1012 rows due to missing values
obj$adjust_batch_effect(types = "X", ref = "2")
#> INFO  [2022-09-26 16:55:20] Adjusting both FI and biorad values
g_post <- obj$plot_pca()
#> WARN  [2022-09-26 16:55:21] Removed -1012 rows due to missing values
ggpubr::ggarrange(g_pre, g_post, labels = "AUTO")

    

df <- obj$df_cmp(types = "X", wide = FALSE)[, .(value = median(value, na.rm = TRUE)), by = c("bp", "variable", "adjusted")]
ggplot(df, aes(bp, value, color = adjusted)) + geom_point() + facet_wrap(~variable, scales = "free_y") + coord_flip() + obj$my_theme

    Adjusting plate effects 

    obj$set_batch(batch = c("1","2"))
#> WARN  [2022-09-26 16:55:30] Only using samples from batch(es) 1Only using samples from batch(es) 2
obj$set_type(type = "X")
#> WARN  [2022-09-26 16:55:30] Only using samples of type X
g_pre <- obj$plot_pca(color = "plate")

obj$set_batch(batch = c("2"))
#> WARN  [2022-09-26 16:55:31] Only using samples from batch(es) 2
obj$adjust_plate_effect(types = "X", ref_study = "overtid", ref_time = 1)
#> INFO  [2022-09-26 16:55:31] Adjusting both FI and biorad values

obj$set_batch(batch = c("1"))
#> WARN  [2022-09-26 16:55:33] Only using samples from batch(es) 1
obj$adjust_plate_effect(types = "X", ref_study = "pregmet1", ref_time = 1)
#> INFO  [2022-09-26 16:55:33] Adjusting both FI and biorad values
obj$adjust_plate_effect(types = "X", ref_study = "normalflow", ref_time = 1)
#> INFO  [2022-09-26 16:55:35] Adjusting both FI and biorad values

obj$set_batch(batch = c("1","2"))
#> WARN  [2022-09-26 16:55:36] Only using samples from batch(es) 1Only using samples from batch(es) 2
g_post <- obj$plot_pca(color = "plate")
ggpubr::ggarrange(g_pre, g_post, labels = "AUTO")
